description: An Alaska Airlines flight in Nashville was forced to halt its takeoff to prevent a potential collision with a Southwest Airlines plane. The sudden stop caused the Alaska jet's tires to go flat but resulted in no injuries. Federal agencies are investigating the incident, and passengers were later flown to Seattle on another aircraft.
title: How quick action by Alaska Airlines pilot prevented near-collision

description: Vladimir Putin warned that if Ukraine is allowed to use Western long-range missiles against Russian territory, it would mean direct involvement of Nato countries in the conflict. He emphasized that this decision would change the nature of the war and force Russia to take appropriate measures, highlighting Nato's role in missile targeting support.
title: 'Will be fighting with Russia if ...': Putin's stark warning to West

description: The one-off Test between Afghanistan and New Zealand was officially abandoned after five days of continuous rain at Greater Noida. This marks just the eighth instance in Test cricket history where a match has been called off without a single ball being bowled. Persistent rainfall prevented even the toss from taking place.
title: Afghan vs NZ Test washed out without ball being bowled at Greater Noida

description: A forensic report has confirmed that two friends of BJP state president Chandrashekhar Bawankule’s son, Sanket, were under the influence of alcohol during a hit-and-run incident in Nagpur. Blood samples taken seven hours after the accident showed alcohol presence. Police are contemplating legal actions against Sanket, who was also present in the car.
title: Maharashtra BJP chief son's 2 friends confirmed drunk 7 hours after accident

description: A doctor and two staff members were arrested in Samastipur for allegedly attempting to rape a nurse at a private clinic. The nurse defended herself using a blade and contacted the police. The incident occurred at a physiotherapy clinic, with the accused reportedly under the influence of alcohol.
title: Nurse mutilates drunk doctor's private parts with blade, escapes rape bid

description: Earlier on Wednesday, DCP Mumbai Police, Raj Tilak Roshan, informed the media that the body of the deceased had been sent for a postmortem.
